"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938602","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>Whilst the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency is reviewing its approach to glucose monitoring technology, the current provision is that drivers are still required to test using finger prick/capillary glucose values, rather than using values from flash glucose monitoring.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-07-19T15:23:20.167Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938602/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938602/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938602/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-11","Diabetes: Driving","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department has made an assessment of the effect on people living with diabetes of the changes to the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) guidelines on driving and diabetes given that NICE recommends that healthcare professionals take the DVLA’s guidance into account when offering glucose monitoring technology.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","163211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938603","Home Office","false","2018-07-20","<p>The Government’s focus remains on protecting those selling sex from harm and enabling the police to target those who exploit vulnerable people involved in prostitution. To this end, the Government has provided over £2m to organisations supporting those involved in prostitution and sex work, including £650,000 from the Violence Against Women and Girls Service Transformation Fund to Merseyside PCC, to provide a victim-focused service for sex workers who are victims, or at risk of sexual or domestic violence and abuse, exploitation or human trafficking.</p><p>The Government recognises the need for research on the nature and prevalence of prostitution before we consider any changes to underlying legislation and policy and have committed £150,000 to fund a research project being undertaken by the University of Bristol.</p><p>To support the police to tackle organised sex-trafficking and other forms of modern slavery, the Government has provided £8.5m of additional funding to the police in England and Wales to provide bespoke and dedicated modern slavery capabilities. This police activity is supported at a national level by the National Crime Agency who lead multiagency operations to target key thematic slavery and trafficking threats including organised sexual exploitation.</p><p> </p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-07-20T13:39:06.213Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938603/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938603/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938603/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-11","Prostitution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps he is taking to tackle organised sexual exploitation.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","163153"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938604","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-07-17","<p>The Government does not hold data on the average length of pay between assignment contracts. Alongside the Government response to Matthew Taylor’s review of modern working practices, we launched a public consultation that covers, amongst other areas, the issue of pay between assignment contracts. As part of this, we asked for information on the use of these contracts. The consultation recently closed. We are considering the responses and we will set out next steps shortly.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-07-17T17:00:53.36Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938604/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938604/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938604/answer","Watford","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938604/answer/previousversion/69818","Biography information for Richard Harrington","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-07-11","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect of pay between assignment (PBA) contracts on equal pay; what the average length of time workers have been on PBA contracts in the most recent period for which figures are available; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Dame Louise Ellman","163002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938605","Home Office","false","2018-07-20","<p>The Government is committed to supporting potential victims of modern slavery to rebuild their lives.</p><p>There are a number of practical reasons why the Government is unable to provide an accurate figure for the number of confirmed victims who have been re-trafficked after leaving the National Referral Mechanism. For example, some victims may not wish to maintain contact when they leave the National Referral Mechanism.</p><p>We are working with the National Crime Agency to improve our ability to identify potential re-trafficking cases. Our reforms to introduce a new digital referral process and to provide access to ‘drop-in’ services for 6 months after confirmed victims have left Government-funded support will also improve our ability to identify re-trafficking for this cohort of victims.</p><p> </p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-07-20T12:06:02.977Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938605/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938605/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938605/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-11","Human Trafficking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many confirmed victims of human trafficking have been subsequently re-trafficked after they have left the National Referral Mechanism.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","163154"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938606","Department for Education","false","2018-07-16","<p>The numbers and identities of children educated at home are not collected centrally.</p><p>For that reason it is not possible to make any overall assessment of the education they receive compared with children attending school. The parents of children of compulsory school age are responsible for ensuring that they receive an efficient full-time education suitable to the child’s age, ability, aptitudes and any special educational needs. The government has made it clear that it believes that the majority of parents undertake this task successfully and with enthusiasm. When the home education being provided is not suitable, the local authority has power to intervene. The existing framework for intervention by local authorities is currently under review. The department is now considering the responses made to the recent consultation on revised guidance for local authorities on the most effective use of their powers in relation to home education, and an associated call for evidence, which closed on 2 July 2018.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-07-16T15:59:41.453Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938606/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938606/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938606/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-07-11","Home Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment his Department has made of whether home-schooled children receive the same level of social and academic education as children attending school.","false","Biography information for Wera Hobhouse","Bath","Wera Hobhouse","163179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938607","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-20","<p>When it comes to determining a fair reimbursement price for new products similar to those already listed in the Drugs Tariff, NHS Prescription Services (part of the NHS Business Service Authority) will aim to ensure that the agreed price is broadly in line with comparable products.</p><p> </p><p>The Department and NHS Prescription Services have a duty to ensure that the National Health Service gets value for money. Therefore, applicants requesting a listing for new products or treatment regimens for which there are no listed comparators should provide satisfactory evidence of improved outcomes/savings/patient benefits commensurate with the requested price. Before any medical device is listed in the Tariff, NHS Prescription Services will negotiate a fair reimbursement with the applicant.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-07-20T09:36:07.97Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938607/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938607/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938607/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-11","Diabetes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the potential of (a) outcome-based payment models and (b) risk sharing partnerships with industry to improve access to diabetes technology to support (i) monitoring, (ii) self-management and (iii) prevention.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","163212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938608","Home Office","false","2018-07-20","<p>On 8 March we launched a 12 week public consultation on proposals for a landmark domestic abuse Bill and a supporting package of practical action to transform the response to domestic abuse. The consultation closed on 31 May. Over 3,200 responses to the consultation were received. The responses to the consultation are being considered and a draft Bill will be published later this session.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-07-20T12:07:38.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938608/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938608/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938608/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-11","Domestic Abuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the timetable is for his next steps in bringing forward a draft Domestic Abuse Bill.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","163155"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938609","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>Clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) are responsible for commissioning diabetes services to meet the requirements of their population. In doing so, CCGs need to ensure that the services they provide are fit for purpose, reflect the needs of the local population and are based on the available evidence and take into account national guidelines.</p><p> </p><p>In this case the relevant guidelines are published by the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence ‘Evidence-based recommendations on continuous subcutaneous insulin infusion (insulin pump therapy) for treating type 1 diabetes in adults and children’ is available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ta151" target="_blank">https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/ta151</a></p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-07-19T15:06:27.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938609/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938609/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938609/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-11","Diabetes: Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps he is taking to increase the uptake of insulin pumps for people throughout England with type 1 diabetes.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","163213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938610","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-07-16","<p>The headquarters for the regular Regiments associated with each Devolved Nation are:</p><p>Scotland:</p><p>The Royal Scots Dragoon Guards - Edinburgh</p><p>19th Regiment Royal Artillery - Tidworth</p><p>Scots Guards - London</p><p>The Royal Regiment of Scotland - Edinburgh</p><p>Wales:</p><p>The Queen's Dragoon Guards - Cardiff</p><p>Welsh Guards - London</p><p>The Royal Welsh - Cardiff</p><p>Northern Ireland:</p><p>Irish Guards - London</p><p>The Royal Irish Regiment - Holywood</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-07-16T15:16:47.547Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938610/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938610/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938610/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-07-11","Army","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, where each headquarters is of regiments from (a) Scotland, (b) Wales and (c) Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","163030"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938611","Home Office","false","2018-09-03","<p>Drugs are illegal where there is scientific and medical evidence that they are harmful to health and society. The possession of any amount of a controlled drug is a criminal offence and the supply of a controlled drug is an even more serious offence. No illegal drug-taking can be assumed to be safe and there is no safe way to take them.</p><p>The Government’s approach remains clear: we must prevent illicit drug use in our communities and help those dependent on drugs to recover, while ensuring our drug laws are enforced. In relation to drug testing at festivals, chief constables are responsible for operational decisions in their local area and we are not standing in their way. We are exploring with the National Police Chiefs’ Council whether their advice on this issue needs to be clarified.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-09-03T15:35:18.223Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938611/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938611/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938611/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-11","Drugs: Misuse","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on drug-related fatalities of drug safety testing at (a) festivals, (b) nightclubs and (c) other large gatherings of young people.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","163156"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938612","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-19","<p>Tameside and Glossop Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG) has established a Diabetes Improvement Group – working with Tameside and Glossop Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust – to deliver improvements and address issues relating to local diabetes care. A recent presentation to local general practitioners (GPs) included data on primary care performance, including structured education.</p><p> </p><p>The Diabetes Improvement Group has identified structured education as a key project. The National Diabetes Audit data for 2016/17 and 2017/18 show that Tameside and Glossop CCG has referred more than 90% of diabetes patients to structured education.</p><p> </p><p>North Derbyshire CCG is aware of a local issue with coding in GP practice systems and has been working with practices to resolve it. The CCG advises that this will have a positive impact on the recording of diabetes education take-up levels.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-07-19T15:04:18.43Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938612/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938612/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938612/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-11","Diabetes: Derbyshire and Tameside","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, for what reason the uptake of structured education programmes among people with type (a) 1 and (b) 2 diabetes in the CCG area of (i) Tameside and Glossop and (ii) North Derbyshire is low; whether he is taking steps to improve that uptake; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","163214"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938613","Home Office","false","2018-07-20","<p>The Modern Slavery Strategy and Implementation Group (MSSIG), brings together key stakeholders including civil society to support the implementation of the Government’s modern slavery strategy.</p><p>The group meets quarterly. The last meeting took place on 24 October 2017. Unfortunately, the meeting scheduled for May 2018 was postponed. The next meeting will take place shortly after recess on 10 September.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-07-20T13:37:22.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938613/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938613/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938613/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-11","Modern Slavery Strategy and Implementation Group","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 26 June 2018 to Question 154594, whether the next meeting of the Modern Slavery Strategy and Implementation Group has been arranged; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","163157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938614","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-07-16","<p>There are ten resettlement centres for people leaving the Armed Forces, run by the Careers Transition Partnership on behalf of the Ministry of Defence (MOD). The locations of the centres are shown at https://www.ctp.org.uk/contact-us.</p><p>Medical rehabilitation for all Armed Forces personnel, including those preparing to leave the Services, is provided by the Defence Medical Rehabilitation Centre, currently located at Headley Court in Surrey. When personnel leave the Armed Forces their healthcare becomes the responsibility of the NHS, although the MOD continues to provide a range of services in support of veterans.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-07-16T15:22:45.473Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938614/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938614/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938614/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-07-11","Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, where each (a) resettlement and (b) rehabilitation centre is for people leaving the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","163031"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938615","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-07-16","<p>The requested information is provided in the attached tables, based on single Service estimates. In the time available, it has not been possible to provide information for the Army. I will write to the hon Member with that information in due course.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-07-16T15:20:03.97Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938615/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938615/answer","163032 - Ian C Lucas.docx","Proportion of Armed Forces recruits from the UK","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938615/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-07-11","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many and what proportion of recruits to the armed forces came from (a) Scotland, (b) Wales, (c) Northern Ireland and (d) England in each of the last 5 years.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","163032"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938616","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-07-17","<p>VisitBritain and VisitEngland are responsible for promoting the UK as a tourist destination, through a range of different initiatives and campaigns. The following table shows the funding that has been spent on promoting England and developing English tourism product since 2010. It includes activity focused on both domestic and international visitors:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>Expenditure (£k)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>10,807</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>9,900</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>11,049</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>10,214</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>10,142</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>7,935</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>18,684</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>16,298</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>18,444</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>113,473</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2018-07-17T10:02:04.587Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938616/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938616/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938616/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-07-11","Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how much money was spent on advertising the activity of touring in England to the UK market in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","163017"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938617","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-07-16","<p>The UK has benefited greatly from the long-standing collaboration on nuclear deterrence and nuclear propulsion with the US. Under the 1958 Mutual Defence Agreement, both nations are able to exchange information and material which enables us to maintain safe, secure and effective nuclear stockpiles, propulsion and weapons systems. Collaboration and co-operation brings enormous advantages for both parties.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-07-16T16:50:38.89Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938617/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938617/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938617/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-07-11","Trident Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what estimate he has made of the value of efficiencies created for the Dreadnought class ballistic missile submarine as a result of cooperation with the United States.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","163023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938618","Department for Education","false","2018-07-16","<p>There have been 64,830 apprenticeship starts in Health, Public Services and Care, reported to date, in the first three quarters of the 2017 to 2018 academic year (August 2017 to April 2018) in England:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/fe-data-library-apprenticeships</a>.</p><p>We want to increase the number of nursing apprenticeships and now have a complete apprentice pathway from entry level to postgraduate advanced clinical practice in nursing. This will support people from all backgrounds to enter a nursing career in the NHS.</p><p>The registered nurse (degree) apprenticeship standard was approved for delivery on 9 May 2017. To date, there have been 260 starts on the registered nurse (degree) apprenticeship in the 2017 to 2018 academic year (August 2017 to April 2018) in England.</p><p>We have also created a new programme for nursing associate (Level 5 standard approved for delivery on 20 November 2017) apprentices to broaden the routes into the profession. 5,000 starts are planned in 2018, with a further 7,500 in 2019. To date, there have been 640 starts on the nursing associate apprenticeship in the 2017 to 2018 academic year (August 2017 to April 2018) in England.</p><p>We are working closely with employers, Health Education England and ministers in the Department of Health and Social Care to make sure the NHS is fully supported to recruit apprentices, both in nursing and in a range of other occupations.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-07-16T13:57:06.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938618/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938618/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938618/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-07-11","Nurses: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many students started a nursing degree apprenticeship in 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","163190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938619","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-07-16","<p>There are no circumstances in which a claimant has been refused an exception where they meet the conditions and have provided relevant evidence to support their request.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-07-16T17:05:22.87Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938619/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938619/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938619/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-07-11","Child Tax Credit and Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many claims have been rejected under each exception to the two child limit for (a) child tax credits and (b) universal credit.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","163137"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938620","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-16","<p>There is no recruitment target for the nurse degree apprenticeship. The Government has a clear aspiration that once the apprentice route is established, up to 1,000 apprentice nurses could join the National Health Service each year.</p><p> </p><p>The registered nurse (degree) apprenticeship standard was approved for delivery on 9 May 2017. To date, there have been 260 starts on the registered nurse (degree) apprenticeship in the 2017 to 2018 academic year (August 2017 to April 2018) in England but this will continue to increase over the full year August 2017 to August 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has no immediate plans to provide additional funding for the costs of education for the nurse degree apprenticeship, which should be met from the apprentice levy.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","163192","2018-07-16T17:04:33.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938620/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938620/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938620/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-11","Nurses: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what his Department's recruitment target is for the nursing degree apprenticeship entry route, and what recent steps his Department has taken to meet that target.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","163191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938621","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-07-16","<p>There is no recruitment target for the nurse degree apprenticeship. The Government has a clear aspiration that once the apprentice route is established, up to 1,000 apprentice nurses could join the National Health Service each year.</p><p> </p><p>The registered nurse (degree) apprenticeship standard was approved for delivery on 9 May 2017. To date, there have been 260 starts on the registered nurse (degree) apprenticeship in the 2017 to 2018 academic year (August 2017 to April 2018) in England but this will continue to increase over the full year August 2017 to August 2018.</p><p> </p><p>The Department has no immediate plans to provide additional funding for the costs of education for the nurse degree apprenticeship, which should be met from the apprentice levy.</p><p> </p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","163191","2018-07-16T17:04:33.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938621/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938621/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938621/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-07-11","Nurses: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what additional finding his Department plans to provide to employers to cover the educational costs of nursing degree apprenticeships.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","163192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938622","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-07-16","<p>The number of offenders convicted in North Wales, broken down by (a) offence group, and (b) offence, can be found in the ‘Court Outcomes by Police Force Area data tool’ at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/criminal-justice-system-statistics-quarterly-december-2017</a></p><p> </p><p>To produce the data requested, click anywhere on the table to open the ‘field list’ and then re-create the following steps:</p><ul><li>Drag and drop ‘Police Force Area’ from the ‘rows’ box into the ‘filters’ box;</li><li>Filter by ‘Police Force Area’ and select North Wales;</li><li>Filter by ‘Convicted/Not Convicted’ and select Convicted;</li><li>Filter by ‘Court Type’ and select all;</li><li>Drag and drop ‘Offence’ from the ‘filters’ box into the ‘rows’ box.</li></ul><p> </p><p>Other categories of interest can be found in the ‘filters’ section of the pivot table.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-07-16T15:33:28.333Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938622/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938622/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938622/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-07-11","Convictions: North Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many convictions for criminal offences were committed in North Wales for each (a) category and (b) offence in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Ian C. Lucas","Wrexham","Ian C. Lucas","163033"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938623","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-07-16","<p>The number of families receiving a child disability element in their child tax credit award is available on the HMRC website here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-and-working-tax-credits-statistics-finalised-annual-awards-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-and-working-tax-credits-statistics-finalised-annual-awards-2016-to-2017</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Information on the proportion of those families with a child who qualifies for a lower rather than a higher child disability addition under universal credit is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-07-16T16:40:05.707Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938623/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938623/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938623/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-07-11","Child Tax Credit and Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many families receive a child disability element in their child tax credit award; and what proportion of those families have a child who  qualifies for a lower rather than a higher child disability addition under universal credit.","false","Biography information for Ruth George","High Peak","Ruth George","163215"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938624","Department for Transport","false","2018-07-19","<p>The UK Government fully recognises the social and economic importance of improving connectivity across all parts of the UK. Where there are areas of cross-border interest, my ministerial colleagues and I remain keen to collaborate with our Scottish counterparts and the Department is currently contributing to discussions on the emerging transport proposals in the proposed Borderlands Growth Deal as well as ongoing work in relation to HS2 and the strategic road network.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2018-07-19T13:08:27.28Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938624/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938624/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938624/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-07-11","Transport: Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with the Scottish Government Cabinet Secretary for Transport on cross border transport infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bowie","West Aberdeenshire and Kincardine","Andrew Bowie","163174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938625","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-07-27","<p>Over the last few years, this Government has provided an unprecedented level of support for our vital offshore oil and gas industry that supports more than 300,000 jobs across the UK. Several sectors, including the oil and gas sector have expressed an interest in a sector deal and we are considering seriously these credible industry-led proposals. We intend to take forward some further deals that best meet expectations set out in the White Paper in due course.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-07-27T12:09:49.597Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938625/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938625/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938625/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-07-11","Offshore Industry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what progress has been made on the oil and gas sector deal.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bowie","West Aberdeenshire and Kincardine","Andrew Bowie","163175"
