"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938651","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-18","<p>Ministers and officials across Government departments regularly discuss air pollution and how to reduce it.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-18T15:49:32.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938651/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938651/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938651/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-11","Schools: Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 21 June 2018 to Question 153431 on Schools: Air Pollution, when his Department last met officials of the (a) Department for Education and (b) Department for Transport to discuss air quality around schools; and if he will place the minutes of those meetings in the Library.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","163195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938652","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-07-18","<p>Under the national trails 'New Deal' funding formula, Natural England provides funds for the maintenance of national trails, including new England coast path stretches as they commence. In 2018/19 this amounts to £1.81 million.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>For 2018/19, the Pennine Way will receive a total allocation of £199,253 which will be matched locally at a minimum ratio of 3:1 (national:local), so the total amount available will be a minimum of £265,671.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-07-18T14:28:54.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938652/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938652/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938652/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-07-11","Public Footpaths","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 24 January 2018 to Question 123107 on Public Footpaths, what funding he plans to allocate to national trails for 2018-19; and how much funding his Department has allocated for 2018-19 to maintain the Pennine Way.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","163196"
