"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938725","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-07-16","<p>The Zimbabwe Government recognised their legal obligation to pay for pensions of former Southern Rhodesia civil servants in a letter from the Minister of Public Service, Labour and Social Welfare on 28 October 2016. Representatives from the British Embassy in Harare regularly raise the requirement of the Government of Zimbabwe to pay these pensions with the Zimbabwean Government and will continue to do so.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-07-16T15:16:37.4Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938725/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938725/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938725/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-07-11","Southern Rhodesia: Civil Servants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether he plans to pay the pension arrears owing to the former members of HM's overseas civil service who remained at their posts after Southern Rhodesia became independent.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","162948"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938726","Home Office","false","2018-07-16","<p>We are considering how we can most effectively implement a registration scheme for EU citizens arriving during the implementation period, alongside the EU Settlement Scheme, and will be setting out more details in due course.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-07-16T15:36:24.34Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938726/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938726/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938726/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-07-11","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if his Department plans to require EU citizens arriving in the UK for the first time during the implementation period and intending to apply for pre-settled status to also register their stay.","false","Biography information for Steve Double","St Austell and Newquay","Steve Double","163144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938727","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-07-18","<p>At the end of May 2010 there were 19,906 people in receipt of State Pension in Linlithgow and East Falkirk. At the end of November 2017 (the latest data available) the number was 20,496.</p><p>Between 2010 and 2017 the full amount of Basic State Pension rose by £1250 per annum in cash terms, which is £660 per annum more than if it had been increased in line with earnings.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2018-07-18T10:02:45.097Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938727/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938727/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/938727/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-07-11","State Retirement Pensions: Linlithgow and East Falkirk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people were in receipt of the state pension in (a) 2010 and (b) 2018 in Linlithgow and East Falkirk constituency.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","163159"
